{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Warnings related to foreign reference types imported from C and C++.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics",
        "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics\/diagnostic-groups"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics\/foreign-reference-type"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Foreign reference types (ForeignReferenceType)"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swift imports C and C++ types annotated with ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SWIFT_SHARED_REFERENCE",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " as",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "foreign reference types",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " (FRTs). Their memory is managed in a similar manner to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "native Swift classes: the compiler automatically inserts calls to retain and",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "release operations that maintain an FRT’s reference count.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When a Swift program calls a foreign function returning an FRT, the compiler",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "relies on ownership convention annotations to determine whether it needs to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "insert a retain call on behalf of the Swift program:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "SWIFT_RETURNS_RETAINED",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " means the FRT is returned as an owned object (+1 reference count)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "SWIFT_RETURNS_UNRETAINED",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " means the FRT is returned as an unowned object (+0 reference count)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Without these annotations, the compiler can generate code with a superfluous or",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "missing retain call that leads to memory leaks and errors, so it emits the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "following warning:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "warning: cannot infer ownership of foreign reference value returned by 'returnsFRT()'"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Fixing-the-warning",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Fixing the warning",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To address these warnings, you should add the appropriate annotation to your",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "C or C++ function declaration:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ Returns a retained (+1) object",
            "SWIFT_RETURNS_RETAINED MyFRT* createObject();",
            "",
            "\/\/ Returns an unretained (+0) object",
            "SWIFT_RETURNS_UNRETAINED MyFRT* getExistingObject();"
          ],
          "syntax" : "cpp",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Objective-C and Objective-C++ methods can be similarly annotated:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ Returns a retained (+1) object",
            "- (MyFRT *)createObject SWIFT_RETURNS_RETAINED;",
            "",
            "\/\/ Returns an unretained (+0) object",
            "- (MyFRT *)getExistingObject SWIFT_RETURNS_UNRETAINED;"
          ],
          "syntax" : "objc",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
